Latency isn't super worth paying attention too, if you can get them tighter than that's good.
The thing is with every new gen of RAM latency values have actually crept up.
Clock even back when with like 8-8-8-12 timings or whatever all th emagazines always told you to chase clocks.
3600CL16 has a slightly higher "true latency" than 3200CL14, BUT testing has shown that it can result in significant gains over the latter
Keep in mind, this is Ryzen specific
So, 3600CL16 is a latency of 8.89ns, 3200CL14 at 8.75ns
